WEBVTT

00:18.900 --> 00:22.080
There never was such an overturn in this world.

00:22.740 --> 00:25.800
Each of these six men was as though he had been struck.

00:26.440 --> 00:29.980
But with silver, the blow passed him almost instantly.

00:30.860 --> 00:34.940
Every thought of his soul had been set full stretch like a racer on that money.

00:35.620 --> 00:41.460
Well, he was brought up in a single second, dead, and he kept his head, found his temper,

00:41.920 --> 00:45.900
and changed his plan before the others had had time to realize the disappointment.

00:47.060 --> 00:50.800
Jim, he whispered, take that and stand by for trouble.

00:52.000 --> 00:54.340
And he passed me a double-barreled pistol.

00:55.360 --> 01:00.780
At the same time he began quietly moving northward, and in a few steps had put the

01:00.780 --> 01:06.040
hollow between us two and the other five. Then he looked at me and nodded as much to say,

01:06.480 --> 01:12.640
here is a narrow corner as indeed I thought it was. His looks were not quite friendly,

01:12.660 --> 01:17.740
and I was so revolted at these constant changes that I could not forbear whispering,

01:18.280 --> 01:20.660
so you've changed sides again.

01:21.660 --> 01:27.580
There was no time left for him to answer in. The buccaneers with oaths and cries began to

01:27.580 --> 01:33.200
leap one after the other into the pit and to dig with their fingers, throwing the boards aside

01:33.200 --> 01:39.280
as they did so. Morgan found a piece of gold. He held it up with a perfect spout of oaths.

01:39.900 --> 01:44.940
It was a two-guinea piece, and it went from hand to hand among them for a quarter of a minute.

01:45.720 --> 01:51.900
Two guineas roared Mary, shaking in at Silver. That's your seven hundred thousand pounds, is it?

01:52.360 --> 01:56.660
You're the man for bargains, ain't you? You're him that never bungled nothing,

01:56.860 --> 02:02.860
you wooded-headed lubber. Dig away, boys, said Silver with the coolest insolence.

02:03.300 --> 02:09.580
You'll find some pig nuts, and I shouldn't wonder. Pig nuts, repeated Mary in a scream.

02:09.580 --> 02:14.580
Mates, do you hear that? I tell you now that man there knew it all along.

02:14.800 --> 02:17.540
Look in the face of him, and you'll see it wrote there.

02:18.440 --> 02:24.720
Ah, Mary, remarked Silver, standing for captain again. You're a pushing lad, to be sure.

02:25.740 --> 02:31.400
But this time everyone was entirely in Mary's favour. They began to scramble out of the

02:31.400 --> 02:38.540
excavation, darting furious glances behind them. One thing I observed, which looked well for us,

02:38.540 --> 02:45.500
they all got out upon the opposite side from Silver. Well, there we stood, two on one side,

02:45.580 --> 02:51.520
five on the other, the pit between us, and nobody screwed up high enough to offer the first blow.

02:52.420 --> 02:59.060
Silver never moved. He watched them, very upright on his crutch, and looked as cool as ever I saw

02:59.060 --> 03:06.020
him. He was brave, and no mistake. At last Mary seemed to think a speech might help matters.

03:06.800 --> 03:13.240
Mates, he said, there's two of them alone there. One, the old cripple that brought us all here,

03:13.380 --> 03:18.160
and blundered us down to this. The other's that cub that I meant to have the heart of.

03:18.240 --> 03:24.540
Now, Mates, he was just raising his arm and his voice, and plainly meant to lead the charge.

03:25.220 --> 03:31.460
But just then, crack, crack, crack, three musket shots flashed out of the thicket.

03:32.000 --> 03:38.440
Mary tumbled head foremost into the excavation. The man with the bandage spun round like a

03:38.440 --> 03:43.940
teetotem, and fell all his length upon his side where he lay dead, but still twitching,

03:44.320 --> 03:47.520
and the other three turned and ran for it with all their might.

03:49.400 --> 03:54.660
Before you could wink, Long John had fired two barrels of a pistol into the struggling Mary,

03:54.660 --> 03:58.440
and as the man rolled up his eyes at him in the last agony,

03:59.420 --> 04:06.740
George, said he, I reckon I settled you. At that same moment, the doctor,

04:07.080 --> 04:13.080
Gray, and Ben Gunn joined us with smoking muskets from among the nutmeg trees.

04:14.220 --> 04:19.240
Forward, cried the doctor, double quick, my lads, we must head them off the boats.

04:20.020 --> 04:25.300
And we set off at a greater pace, sometimes plunging through the bushes to the chest.

04:26.440 --> 04:31.700
I tell you, but Silver was anxious to keep up with us. The work that man went through,

04:32.020 --> 04:35.860
leaping on his crutch until the muscles of his chest were fit to burst,

04:36.360 --> 04:42.940
was work no sound man ever equaled, and so thinks the doctor. As it was, he was already

04:42.940 --> 04:47.920
thirty yards behind us, and on the verge of strangling when we reached the brow of the slope.

04:49.100 --> 04:57.100
Doctor, he hailed, see there, no hurry. Sure enough, there was no hurry. In a more open

04:57.100 --> 05:02.100
part of the plateau, we could see the three survivors still running in the same direction

05:02.100 --> 05:07.980
as they had started, right for the mizzenmast hill. We were already between them and the boats,

05:08.440 --> 05:14.740
and so we sat, four of us, down to breathe, while Long John, mopping his face, came slowly up with

05:14.740 --> 05:22.360
us. Thank ye kindly, doctor, says he. You came in at about the nick, I guess, for me and Hawkins.

05:23.340 --> 05:27.680
And so it's you, Ben Gunn, he added. Well, you're a nice one, to be sure.

05:28.460 --> 05:34.340
I'm Ben Gunn, I am, replied the maroon, wriggling like an eel in his embarrassment.

05:35.120 --> 05:41.480
And, he added, after a long pause, how do, Mr. Silver? Pretty well, I think ye, says you.

05:42.260 --> 05:47.120
Ben, Ben, murmured Silver, to think as you've done me.

05:48.520 --> 05:55.180
The doctors sent back Gray for one of the pickaxes deserted in their flight by the mutineers, and then

05:55.180 --> 06:00.600
as we proceeded leisurely downhill to where the boats were lying, related in a few words what had

06:00.600 --> 06:07.100
taken place. It was a story that profoundly interested Silver, and Ben Gunn, the half-idiot

06:07.100 --> 06:13.960
of the maroon, was the hero from beginning to end. Ben, in his long, lonely wanderings about

06:13.960 --> 06:20.000
the island, had found the skeleton. It was he that had rifled it. He had found the treasure.

06:20.180 --> 06:27.260
He had dug it up. It was the haft of his pickaxe that lay broken in the excavation. He had carried

06:27.260 --> 06:33.780
it on his back in many weary journeys, from the foot of the tall pine to a cave he had on the

06:33.780 --> 06:39.100
two-pointed hill at the northeast angle of the island, and there it had lain stored in safety

06:39.100 --> 06:46.580
since two months before the arrival of the hispanola. When the doctor had wormed this secret from him on

06:46.580 --> 06:52.940
the afternoon of the attack, and when next morning he saw the anchorage deserted, he had gone to

06:52.940 --> 06:59.520
Silver, given him the chart, which was now useless, given him the stores, for Ben Gunn's cave was well

06:59.520 --> 07:05.440
supplied with goatsmeat salted by himself, given anything and everything to get a chance of moving

07:05.440 --> 07:11.660
in safety from the stockade to the two-pointed hill, there to be clear of malaria and keep a

07:11.660 --> 07:18.880
guard upon the money. As for you, Jim, he said, it went against my heart, but I did what I thought

07:18.880 --> 07:24.720
best for those who had stood by their duty, and if you were not one of these, whose fault was it?

07:25.940 --> 07:31.440
That morning, finding that I was to be involved in the horrid disappointment he had prepared for

07:31.440 --> 07:37.420
the mutineers, he had run all the way to the cave, and leaving the squire to guard the captain,

07:37.600 --> 07:43.380
had taken Gray and the maroon, and started making the diagonal across the island to be at hand beside

07:43.380 --> 07:50.380
the pine. Soon, however, he saw that our party had the start of him, and Ben Gunn, being fleet of foot,

07:50.380 --> 07:57.140
had been dispatched in front to do his best alone. Then it had occurred to him to work upon the

07:57.140 --> 08:02.880
superstitions of his former shipmates, and he was so far successful that Gray and the doctors had

08:02.880 --> 08:06.940
come up and were already ambushed before the arrival of the treasure hunters.

08:08.300 --> 08:15.620
Ah, said Silver, it were fortunate for me that I had Hawkins here. You would have let old John

08:15.620 --> 08:22.540
be cut to bits and never given it a thought, doctor. Not a thought, replied Dr. Livesey cheerily.

08:23.980 --> 08:29.120
And by this time we had reached the gigs. The doctor with his pickaxe demolished one of them,

08:29.460 --> 08:34.060
and then we all got aboard the other and set out to go round by sea for North Inlet.

08:35.780 --> 08:41.940
This was a run of eight or nine miles. Silver, though he was almost killed already with fatigue,

08:41.940 --> 08:48.300
was set to an oar, like the rest of us, and we were soon skimming swiftly over a smooth sea.

08:49.420 --> 08:53.660
Soon we passed out of the straits and doubled the southeast corner of the island,

08:53.920 --> 08:56.860
round which four days ago we had towed the Hispaniola.

08:58.040 --> 09:03.020
As we passed the two-pointed hill we could see the black mouth of Ben Gunn's cave,

09:03.200 --> 09:09.160
and a figure standing by it, leaning on a musket. It was the squire, and we waved a

09:09.160 --> 09:14.580
handkerchief and gave him three cheers, in which the voice of silver joined as heartily as any.

09:16.340 --> 09:19.440
Three miles farther, just inside the mouth of North Inlet,

09:20.140 --> 09:26.420
what should we meet but the Hispaniola cruising by herself? The last flood had lifted her,

09:26.540 --> 09:30.760
and had there been much wind or a strong tide current as in the southern anchorage,

09:31.120 --> 09:35.180
we should never have found her more, or found her stranded beyond help.

09:35.820 --> 09:39.300
As it was, there was little amiss beyond the wreck of the mainsail.

09:40.260 --> 09:45.020
Another anchor was got ready and dropped in a fathom and a half of water. We all pulled

09:45.020 --> 09:50.820
round again to Rum Cove, the nearest point for Ben Gunn's treasure house, and then Gray,

09:51.120 --> 09:56.540
single-handed, returned with the gig to the Hispaniola where he was to pass the night on guard.

09:58.000 --> 10:01.460
A gentle slope ran up from the beach to the entrance of the cave.

10:01.460 --> 10:06.340
At the top, the squire met us. To me, he was cordial and kind,

10:06.460 --> 10:10.200
saying nothing of my escapade either in the way of blame or praise.

10:10.980 --> 10:13.870
At Silver's polite salute, he somewhat flushed.

10:15.540 --> 10:22.660
John Silver, he said, you are a prodigious villain, an imposter, a monstrous imposter, sir.

10:23.200 --> 10:30.280
I am told I am not to prosecute you. Well, then I will not. But the dead men, sir,

10:30.280 --> 10:36.880
hang about your neck like millstones. Thank you kindly, sir, replied Long John,

10:37.080 --> 10:44.700
again saluting. I dare you to thank me, cried the squire. It is a gross dereliction of my duty.

10:44.960 --> 10:49.140
Stand back. And thereupon we all entered the cave.

10:50.100 --> 10:55.560
It was a large, airy place with a little spring and a pool of clear water overhung with ferns.

10:56.200 --> 11:00.820
The floor was sand. Before a big fire lay Captain Smollett,

11:01.020 --> 11:07.660
and in a far corner only duskily flickered over by the blaze, I beheld great heaps of coin and

11:07.660 --> 11:14.260
quadrilaterals built of bars of gold. That was Flint's treasure that we had come so far to seek,

11:14.560 --> 11:19.100
and then it cost already the lives of seventeen men from the Hispaniola.

11:19.700 --> 11:23.660
How many it had cost in the amassing, what blood and sorrow,

11:23.660 --> 11:29.200
what good ships scuttled on the deep, what brave men walking the plank blindfold,

11:29.760 --> 11:36.400
what shot of cannon, what shame and lies and cruelty, perhaps no man alive could tell.

11:37.080 --> 11:42.940
Yet there were still three upon that island, Silver and Old Morgan and Ben Gunn,

11:43.300 --> 11:48.740
who had each taken his share in these crimes, as each had hoped in vain to share in the reward.

11:50.040 --> 11:55.220
"'Come in, Jim,' said the Captain. "'You're a good boy in your line, Jim,

11:55.320 --> 12:01.180
but I don't think you and me'll go to sea again. You're too much of the born favorite for me.'

12:01.940 --> 12:05.160
"'Is that you, John Silver? What brings you here, man?'

12:05.900 --> 12:09.140
"'Come back to my duty, sir,' returned Silver.

12:10.320 --> 12:13.760
"'Ah,' said the Captain, and that was all he said.

12:14.840 --> 12:20.920
"'What a supper I had of it that night, with all my friends around me, and what a meal it was,

12:21.060 --> 12:27.140
with Ben Gunn's salted goat and some delicacies and a bottle of old wine from the Hispaniola.

12:27.760 --> 12:34.380
Never, I am sure, were people gayer or happier. And there was Silver, sitting back almost out

12:34.380 --> 12:39.320
of the firelight, but eating heartily, prompt to spring forward when anything was wanted,

12:39.320 --> 12:47.440
even joining quietly in our laughter, the same bland, polite, obsequious seaman of the voyage out."

12:49.020 --> 12:50.200
End of chapter 33

